history.content: The total capacity of the class (incl. undergrads and 289) is expected to be 744 seats, after expansion.

On classes.berekeley it says that "Initial enrollment capacity is set to 70% of total enrollment" while class capacity is set to 410, meaning the actual/total capacity is around 586 seats. However, they also note that "We anticipate total enrollment for the COMBINED class to be 744 seats", which somewhat contradicts the first line. So which one is the actual total capacity? Does the 744 seats include both undergrad and grad students?
history.subject: CS 189 enrollment capacity clarification?
